#. [race], id=AE_agl_harpy
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies.cfg:27
msgid ""
"Harpies, often called bird-people, are humanlike creatures endowed with "
"winged arms. They are thinner and much lighter than humans, and would be "
"shorter than them if not for their long legs. They also bear other birdlikes "
"features, like a feathered tail and clawed, scaly hands and feet. Harpies are"
" prudent creatures, aware of their frailty and quick to flee when they sense "
"danger.\n"
"\n"
"Harpies build simple villages high in cliffs and mountains, sometimes "
"forests, out of reach of most animals and people. Harpy communities are "
"located in isolated places, set either on the shores of the continent or in "
"islands far from the land. They feed on fishes that they catch by plunging or"
" with nets. Harpies that live inland will instead hunt small game and birds, "
"and may also scavenge for fruits. \n"
"Harpies do not sell a lot of goods, as they mostly craft simple tools, "
"weapons and clothes. Their musical instruments are however highly valued by "
"performers and connoisseurs alike. They trade feathers and food to merchants "
"of other races for tools or materials, but most of the time they prefer to "
"use their talents as courriers or scouts. \n"
"\n"
"Harpies use powerful calls and songs to relay messages to other communities. "
"Due to this way of communicating and their fast winged messengers, "
"information travels extremely fast between harpy groups. \n"
"Their tradition is mostly oral. The history and tales of their people are "
"kept by tellers and songstresses held in high regard by the community. "
"Harpies all possess some amount of magic that they can express through their "
"voice. The ones who train to become mages start as minstrels or tellers, "
"training their voice for different purposes, be it mastering the elements or "
"other's minds. \n"
"\n"
"Harpies have a bad reputation among humans, as they have a history of raiding"
" ships and stealing from villages. As they travel by flight, they rarely "
"interact with other races, adding to the existing distrust."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_harpies_Harpy_Ashtail, race=AE_agl_harpy
#. [male]
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Ashtail.cfg:4
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Ashtail.cfg:23
msgid "Harpy Ashtail"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_harpies_Harpy_Ashtail, race=AE_agl_harpy
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Ashtail.cfg:31
msgid ""
"Numerous battles of dousing foes in flames have left scars on the plumage of "
"these veterans. Their peers have named them Ashtails, as their talons and "
"feathers turned grey from their grim duties."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#. [attack], type=fire, range=melee
