#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_harpies_Harpy_Bomber, race=AE_agl_harpy
#. [male]
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Bomber.cfg:4
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Bomber.cfg:22
msgid "Harpy Bomber"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_harpies_Harpy_Bomber, race=AE_agl_harpy
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Bomber.cfg:30
msgid ""
"Harpy bombers are involved in more serious conflicts than simple defense of "
"their colony and as such, they have upgraded their equipment, flying and "
"throwing techniques. In addition to the classic rocks, they also use lighter,"
" flaming projectiles, that earned them their current name."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_harpies_Harpy_Captivator, race=AE_agl_harpy, gender=female
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Captivator.cfg:4
msgid "Harpy Captivator"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_harpies_Harpy_Captivator, race=AE_agl_harpy, gender=female
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Captivator.cfg:21
msgid ""
"The voice of the most famous harpy minstrels is said to be able to both break"
" and mend hearts. People usually regard these stories as mere legends, but "
"some of them suspect there is magic at work. The captivator's first aim is "
"precisely to avoid that people think this.\n"
"They weave magic within their melodies, warping others' perception of the "
"world and disguising their looks to better charm them. When their power is "
"strong enough, their illusions start to occur from nearly inaudible sounds "
"like low humming or breathing, allowing them to change how they look to "
"please their audience."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_harpies_Duke_Of_The_Night, race=AE_agl_harpy
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Dukeofthenight.cfg:4
msgid "Duke of the Night"
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Dukeofthenight.cfg:22
msgid "Duchess of the Night"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_harpies_Duke_Of_The_Night, race=AE_agl_harpy
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Dukeofthenight.cfg:28
msgid ""
"Long ago there was a forest-bound kingdom of many different kin, with its "
"lord and lady known as fierce defenders of the land. But through war it was "
"sullied, and although its invaders withdrew, many lives were lost. Now the "
"forests are void and dark, and at night, one must be careful not to encounter"
" vengeful specters from the past."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=melee
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Dukeofthenight.cfg:117
msgid "prey"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_harpies_Harpy_Emissary, race=AE_agl_harpy
#. [male]
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Emissary.cfg:4
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Emissary.cfg:23
msgid "Harpy Emissary"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_harpies_Harpy_Emissary, race=AE_agl_harpy
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Emissary.cfg:31
msgid ""
"Elite messengers become the quick emissaries of powerful leaders, whom they "
"gained the trust of after decades of work. Swift as the wind, they are "
"matched in speed only by the griffins of the high peaks. As they often carry "
"messages of high importance in troubled times, they can defend themselves "
"quite well by using their sharp talons and unrivalled air mobility. "
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=melee
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Emissary.cfg:123
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Messenger.cfg:118
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Traveller.cfg:114
msgid "sky dive"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_harpies_Harpy_Enchantress, race=AE_agl_harpy, gender=female
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Enchantress.cfg:4
msgid "Harpy Enchantress"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_harpies_Harpy_Enchantress, race=AE_agl_harpy, gender=female
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Enchantress.cfg:22
msgid ""
"The legendary harpy enchantresses are beings admired by the majority of "
"people. They carry themselves with grace and confidence, knowing full well "
"the power they hold over the ordinary folk. Thanks to their influence, they "
"develop a network of connections to support their own goals or those they are"
" given by harpy lorekeepers."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_harpies_Endsinger_Harpy, race=AE_agl_harpy, gender=female
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Endsinger.cfg:4
msgid "Endsinger_Harpy"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_harpies_Endsinger_Harpy, race=AE_agl_harpy, gender=female
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Endsinger.cfg:22
msgid ""
"It is said harpies lived forever in their island of mists. But as they left "
"it to gain true flesh and blood, their everlasting youth was lost, and some "
"sought to reclaim it."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=fire, range=ranged
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Endsinger.cfg:109
msgid "song of extinction"
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=arcane, range=ranged
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Endsinger.cfg:122
msgid "soul drain"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_harpies_Harpy_Falconeer, race=AE_agl_harpy
#. [male]
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Falconeer.cfg:4
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Falconeer.cfg:22
msgid "Harpy Falconeer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_harpies_Harpy_Falconeer, race=AE_agl_harpy
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Falconeer.cfg:30
msgid ""
"Various birds are popular among harpies as pets. Among them, falcons are used"
" for hunting, and warfare when the need arises. Some harpies can easily mimic"
" their calls, granting the bird and its wielder excellent coordination. "
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=blade, range=ranged
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Falconeer.cfg:114
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Featherlord.cfg:136
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Flagbearer.cfg:130
msgid "falcon"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_harpies_Harpy_Featherlord, race=AE_agl_harpy
#. [male]
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Featherlord.cfg:4
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Featherlord.cfg:23
msgid "Harpy Featherlord"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_harpies_Harpy_Featherlord, race=AE_agl_harpy
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Featherlord.cfg:31
msgid ""
"Harpy commanders use their bird companion and specific calls to quickly "
"transmit orders on the battlefield. Their brightly colored flag helps them "
"catch their allies' attention to redirect troops wherever necessary. "
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_harpies_Harpy_Fighter, race=AE_agl_harpy
#. [male]
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Fighter.cfg:4
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Fighter.cfg:22
msgid "Harpy Fighter"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_harpies_Harpy_Fighter, race=AE_agl_harpy
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Fighter.cfg:30
msgid ""
"Harpies can already cause harm with their sharp talons. However, those tasked"
" to fight the colony's foes often reinforce their claws with small blades. "
"Their light gambeson allows them to resist hits slightly better while "
"retaining their kind's mobility. "
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_harpies_Harpy_Flagbearer, race=AE_agl_harpy
#. [male]
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Flagbearer.cfg:4
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Flagbearer.cfg:22
msgid "Harpy Flagbearer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_harpies_Harpy_Flagbearer, race=AE_agl_harpy
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Flagbearer.cfg:30
msgid ""
"The habit of guiding their bird around gives harpies skills in observing and "
"giving out orders, which are applicable in wide scale combat as well. Some "
"falconeers take up the flag-bearing spear to lead their peers in battle, and "
"while their fighting strength is lesser than others', the coordination they "
"bring to the squadron makes it much more deadly. "
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_harpies_Harpy_Flockmaster, race=AE_agl_harpy
#. [male]
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Flockmaster.cfg:4
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Flockmaster.cfg:66
msgid "Harpy Flockmaster"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_harpies_Harpy_Flockmaster, race=AE_agl_harpy
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Flockmaster.cfg:22
msgid ""
"Harpies whose love for birds is extreme spend their life with them, flying "
"and hunting together. With their skilled calls they bring together small "
"flocks of hawks to help them, directing them to reach their goal more "
"efficiently. "
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=blade, range=ranged
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Flockmaster.cfg:46
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Raptortongue.cfg:63
msgid "falcon storm"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_harpies_Harpy_Galesinger, race=AE_agl_harpy, gender=female
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Galesinger.cfg:4
msgid "Harpy Galesinger"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_harpies_Harpy_Galesinger, race=AE_agl_harpy, gender=female
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Galesinger.cfg:20
msgid ""
"Experienced minstrels may decide to become the keepers of harpy knowledge. "
"They spend years learning from their masters the thousands of songs that "
"relate harpy lore. Among these chants are magic spells that allow them to "
"bend the winds to their will, that harpies have used since olden times to "
"travel across the ocean. "
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=cold, range=ranged
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Galesinger.cfg:67
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Songstressofstorms.cfg:68
msgid "Song of gale"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_harpies_Harpy_Messenger, race=AE_agl_harpy
#. [male]
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Messenger.cfg:4
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Messenger.cfg:22
msgid "Harpy Messenger"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_harpies_Harpy_Messenger, race=AE_agl_harpy
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Messenger.cfg:30
msgid ""
"Due to their numerous travels, harpy wanderers end up mingling with other "
"races a lot more. Often they will offer their service as long range "
"messengers to various folk. The time spent hunting in the wild has given them"
" keen eyes which serve them well in battle also. "
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_harpies_Harpy_Minstrel, race=AE_agl_harpy, gender=female
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Minstrel.cfg:4
msgid "Harpy Minstrel"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_harpies_Harpy_Minstrel, race=AE_agl_harpy, gender=female
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Minstrel.cfg:20
msgid ""
"Harpies avoid other races whenever possible, and are seldom welcomed warmly. "
"There is however an exception : minstrels are renowned for their incredible "
"singing. Some say their voice can make anyone fall in awe and completely "
"forget their surroundings. Although the public usually admires their talent, "
"people sometimes fear their supposed powers.\n"
"They wander between towns, living off their art or flying away quickly when "
"they feel threatened. Some of them end up settling down in human cities, but "
"more often than not they keep traveling and act as informants for harpy "
"communities."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=arcane, range=ranged
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Minstrel.cfg:103
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Siren.cfg:159
msgid "beguiling song"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_harpies_Harpy_Phantom, race=AE_agl_harpy
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Nightgaunt.cfg:4
msgid "Harpy Phantom"
msgstr ""

#. [male]
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Nightgaunt.cfg:22
msgid "male^Harpy Phantom"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_harpies_Harpy_Phantom, race=AE_agl_harpy
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Nightgaunt.cfg:28
msgid ""
"When the night is at its darkest, are the shadows not more enticing than "
"ever? Hide in the night, enjoy it, use it, but never forget it is not your "
"friend. Those that fear not the shadows will in time join their ranks.\n"
"-Tales of the owl hunters"
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Nightgaunt.cfg:73
msgid "deathclaws"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_harpies_Night_Harpy, race=AE_agl_harpy
#. [male]
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Nightharpy.cfg:4
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Nightharpy.cfg:21
msgid "Night Harpy"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_harpies_Night_Harpy, race=AE_agl_harpy
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Nightharpy.cfg:29
msgid ""
"While most harpies prefer to build their homes in the caves dotting seashore "
"cliffs and tall mountains, some have chosen to seek shelter in forests. This "
"new environment has made them change their hunting techniques, which now rely"
" on stealth a lot more. Over time their body evolved and they can now fly "
"silently, which makes them extremely hard to notice at night. "
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_harpies_Harpy_Parader, race=AE_agl_harpy, gender=female
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Parader.cfg:4
msgid "Harpy Parader"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_harpies_Harpy_Parader, race=AE_agl_harpy, gender=female
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Parader.cfg:21
msgid ""
"As they better their magical craft, some minstrels take delight in catching "
"other's eyes. Switching focus from songs to dance, their plumage changes to "
"reflect their spell-weaving. Paraders, on the opposite of captivators, mean "
"to be noticed, and distract their foes to give their allies more "
"opportunities. "
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_harpies_Harpy_Pirate, race=AE_agl_harpy
#. [male]
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Pirate.cfg:4
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Pirate.cfg:22
msgid "Harpy Pirate"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_harpies_Harpy_Pirate, race=AE_agl_harpy
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Pirate.cfg:30
msgid ""
"Oftentimes harpy warriors band together to attack trade ships. They use long "
"pikes to attack in a safer way and stay out of reach of melee fighters with "
"their wings. Pirate groups nest on isolated craggy islands where they store "
"their loot before trading it with other harpy colonies. "
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_harpies_Harpy_Raider, race=AE_agl_harpy
#. [male]
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Raider.cfg:4
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Raider.cfg:23
msgid "Harpy Raider"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_harpies_Harpy_Raider, race=AE_agl_harpy
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Raider.cfg:31
msgid ""
"The seasoned harpy soldiers often come from former bandit crews. They lend "
"their talent as mercenaries to various armed forces, who make good use of "
"their ability to strike anywhere quickly. "
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_harpies_Harpy_Raptortongue, race=AE_agl_harpy
#. [male]
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Raptortongue.cfg:4
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Raptortongue.cfg:22
msgid "Harpy Raptortongue"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_harpies_Harpy_Raptortongue, race=AE_agl_harpy
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Raptortongue.cfg:42
msgid ""
"Over time falconeers efficiently learn the falcons' language. As the bird "
"ages their tamer often will bring in new recruits for taming. "
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_harpies_Resplendent_Harpy, race=AE_agl_harpy, gender=female
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Resplendent.cfg:4
msgid "Resplendent Harpy"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_harpies_Resplendent_Harpy, race=AE_agl_harpy, gender=female
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Resplendent.cfg:23
msgid ""
"Resplendent harpies make the most of their dazzling presence to help their "
"allies go unnoticed. In social gatherings where they thrive, they know when "
"to show glitter and when to lay low so as not to displease their host.\n"
"In battle they learnt to be very nimble, avoiding the harm that comes with "
"being the center of attention, and confuse the enemy by making their presence"
" clear or hidden to be harder to catch. "
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_harpies_Harpy_Rockthrower, race=AE_agl_harpy
#. [male]
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Rockthrower.cfg:4
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Rockthrower.cfg:22
msgid "Harpy Rockthrower"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_harpies_Harpy_Rockthrower, race=AE_agl_harpy
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Rockthrower.cfg:30
msgid ""
"One of the simplest tactics that harpies use to defend their homes is to drop"
" rocks on the threat, which is often grounded and dangerous. This method may "
"be tiring and somewhat ineffective due to the relative precision of the "
"shots, but harpies value their safety enough to employ it often."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_harpies_Shrieker, race=AE_agl_harpy
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Shrieker.cfg:4
msgid "Shrieker"
msgstr ""

#. [male]
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Shrieker.cfg:22
msgid "male^Shrieker"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_harpies_Shrieker, race=AE_agl_harpy
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Shrieker.cfg:30
msgid ""
"As the moon hides behind the peaks, the wind in the gloom calls.\n"
"Answer it fast! Answer it quick! Quiet shall be your fall.\n"
"To uncover the night's secrets, won't you heed this soft howl?\n"
"Answer it fast, trust the spirits, run with the winds and wolves.\n"
"Won't you come deeper down the forest, in the shadows with us to dance?\n"
"'Til the morrow, the wind shall rest, and wait for you, for its next chance.\n"
"As the moon returns in white flame, it shall be back for your regrets.\n"
"Answer it well, it knows your name, and certainly never forgets."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=ranged
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Shrieker.cfg:128
msgid "shriek"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_harpies_Harpy_Siren, race=AE_agl_harpy, gender=female
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Siren.cfg:4
msgid "Harpy Siren"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_harpies_Harpy_Siren, race=AE_agl_harpy, gender=female
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Siren.cfg:22
msgid ""
"Harpies have a strong belief that their kind was born from a magical song, "
"sung from what they call the World of Mist. When the wind song feels "
"sorrowful, it is because we hear the laments of beings that got lost in that "
"illusory land."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_harpies_Songstress_Of_Storms, race=AE_agl_harpy, gender=female
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Songstressofstorms.cfg:4
msgid "Songstress of Storms"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_harpies_Songstress_Of_Storms, race=AE_agl_harpy, gender=female
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Songstressofstorms.cfg:21
msgid ""
"Some harpy singers chose to live away from land, secluded in places where "
"they can become one with the wind. They spend days meditating at sea to "
"listen to the song of the gales. When their kin calls for help however, their"
" mastery of weather lets them summon fierce storms that scatter enemy troops."
" "
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=fire, range=ranged
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Songstressofstorms.cfg:80
msgid "Song of storm"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_harpies_Harpy_Stalkerwing, race=AE_agl_harpy
#. [male]
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Stalkerwing.cfg:4
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Stalkerwing.cfg:21
msgid "Harpy Stalkerwing"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_harpies_Harpy_Stalkerwing, race=AE_agl_harpy
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Stalkerwing.cfg:29
msgid ""
"The owl harpies' unparalleled stealth makes them a great asset in wars and "
"skirmishes, where they spy and strike in the midst of enemy lines.\n"
"As they tread further down this path of stalking and hunt, the wisps of magic"
" they possess make them fade more and more within the darkness. "
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_harpies_Harpy_Traveller, race=AE_agl_harpy
#. [male]
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Traveller.cfg:4
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Traveller.cfg:22
msgid "Harpy Traveller"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_harpies_Harpy_Traveller, race=AE_agl_harpy
#: .\units\misc_units\harpies\Traveller.cfg:30
msgid ""
"Harpies by nature see more of the world than non winged folks, and some of "
"them long to see what is beyond the horizon. Those that follow this path are "
"among the fastest and most agile flyers in the sky. "
msgstr ""
